{"word":"ἄγη","slug":"ἄγη","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄγη</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἄγαμαι'><el>ἄγαμαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>wonder, awe, amazement</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>envy, malice</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; and of the gods, <i>jealousy</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}